{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "The NCTM (2000) places great emphasis on the fundamental role of technology in the pedagogical delivery of mathematical concepts, as it profoundly influences both instructional methodologies and content, ultimately augmenting students' educational outcomes.",
    "Educational technology, as set out by Robinson et al. (2008), encompasses the comprehensive investigation and conscientious application of learning facilitation techniques and ethical principles that harness the potential of technological resources and processes.",
    "By incorporating technology in the educational landscape, students are afforded the opportunity to cultivate critical, creative and innovative thinking skills that are indispensable for effective problemsolving within authentic real-world scenarios (Jackson et al., 2012; Way & Beardon, 2003).",
    "Despite its relatively recent emergence, the use of technology in mathematics education presents considerable promise across all educational levels.",
    "However, to ensure the effectiveness of pedagogy, incorporating technology in class requires meticulous planning and conscientious management (Hutkemri & Nordin, 2011)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
